        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 14 at 5:27PM MDT until June 14 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 21 miles south of
Ryegate, or 27 miles north of Columbus, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...At 520 PM, public reported half dollar size hail.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Halfbreed Lake Wildlife, Hailstone Wildlife Refuge, Rapelje and
Molt.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and has
produced large hail.</instruction>
